page.title: 18Woodlands,Longtown,Cumbria.
page.content: DISTRIBUTION:-Widely scattered over the area,in commercial plantations ,shelterbelts,& amenity form,also managed for wildlife & game preservation.TREE-SPECIES:- Scots Pine,Larch,Norway Spruce,Sitka Spruce Douglas Fir,Western Hemlock,Western Red Cedar,Silver Fir,Lawson Cypress, Corsican Pine,HARDWOODS:-Oak,Beech, Hazel,Alder,Willow,Holly,Cherry, Service,Hornbeam.UNDERGROWTH:-Elder, Rowan,Rhododendron,Box,Hawthorn,Privet Blackthorn,Bramble,Broom,Gorse,Heather ,Bracken,Ferns,Snowberry.TIMBER USES:- Joinery,Furniture,Fence Material, Pallet & Packaging,Mining timbers, Firewood,Chipwood,Paper Industry, Rustic Furniture.WILD-LIFE:-Mammals, Roe Deer,Badgers,Foxes,Rabbits,Hares, Stoat,Weasle,Mice,Voles,Red Squirrels Mink,Bats.BIRDS:-Buzzard,Hawk,Kestrel Owls,Pheasant,Partridge,Herons,Mallard
